body surface area. A GFR estimate is validated only for patients greater
than or equal to 18 years of age. Since this test is not useful if renal
function is changing rapidly, a GFR estimate is not reported for inpatients.

content.content:
Early AM (6 - 9 AM) Testosterone levels are usually 10 - 30 % higher than
PM levels in younger men (under 50 years).
Early morning specimen collection is strongly preferred for determining
androgen status in men. Interfering substances may cause false elevations
in testosterone immunoassays at low concentrations. Consider ordering
Testosterone, Total, Pediatric (EAP# 84403G), or for adults, order
Testosterone, Ultrasensitive by LC/MSMS (EAP# 84403K). These tests are
performed at Quest Laboratories and are appropriate for pediatric patients,
adult females, and adult males undergoing testosterone suppression therapy.
